I've gone through background checks with both large and small companies, conducted by internal teams as well as third-party providers. 

In general, the checks focus on the following:
- Criminal record (if any);
- Education history, if you've submitted diploma or degree credentials;
- Employment history over the past five years.

For employment verification, you're usually asked to provide one or more of the following:
- Signed employment or termination agreements showing your official start and end dates;
- Payslips covering relevant periods;
- Contact details of a current employee at the company who can verify your role and dates.

Requirements may vary slightly depending on the company or provider, but that’s the typical scope.
